A man in his fifties was arrested on suspicion of murder this morning after he was seen trying to dump a body in the River Thames.

A witness spotted him trying to drop a  man with serious head injuries into the water at Deptford Wharf in south-east London at 3am.

Scotland Yard said today that officers raced to the scene and stopped the man as he drove off, finding the body in his boot.

London Ambulance Service attended and the man  was pronounced dead at the scene, which is directly across the Thames from Canary Wharf and close to Greenwich.

